raw_data.title: Certified Industrial Hygienist, Certified Safety Professional
raw_data.description: Oversees the work of all staff members. Provides technical guidance and advise to staff.  Conducts industrial hygiene and safety support on complex and large processes and building compounds. Conducts OSHA audits, provides safety consultation, and preforms OSHA safety and health training. Helps to interpret regulatory requirements and ensuring project is in accordance with regulations, professional standards and guidelines. Formally peer reviews, edits and revises technical documents to ensure their accuracy and completeness. Conduct OSHA based safety and health audits. May prepare reports.

raw_data.title: Project Manager Administrative
raw_data.description: Responsible for managing day-to-day project operation and supervision of all industrial hygiene and safety field personnel. Broad breadth of experience and capabilities and ability to direct a wide range of industrial and safety support. Provides recognition, evaluation and controls based on various industrial hygiene and safety data measured and collected from sample analysis. This includes but not limited to mold surveys, water sampling, and safety inspections. Reports directly to the CIH or CSP of the project. Conduct OSHA based safety and health audits. Prepares reports.
